&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Anthropic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic’s mission is to create reliable, interpretable, and steerable AI systems. We want AI to be safe and beneficial for our users and for society as a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together to build beneficial AI systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;heading&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic is seeking an analytical and execution-oriented Sales Strategy &amp;amp; Operations professional to support our Startups sales segment within the Americas region. Reporting to the Head of AMER Sales Strategy and Operations, you will be a key S&amp;amp;O partner to our Startups sales team, driving the operational excellence, analytics, and process design that enable this high-volume, high-velocity segment to scale effectively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Startups segment represents a critical growth vector for Anthropic—serving as the entry point for many of the companies building the next generation of AI-native applications. This segment operates at high velocity with a large volume of accounts, requiring operational infrastructure that balances scale with personalized engagement. You will support a team that manages relationships with early-stage companies, administers the Earlybird credits program, and identifies breakout startups poised for rapid consumption growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has experience supporting high-velocity sales teams, understands the unique dynamics of startup ecosystems, and brings strong analytical skills with attention to operational detail. You thrive in environments where you&#39;re building and refining processes, can translate data into actionable insights, and are excited about the opportunity to shape how Anthropic engages with the startup community.&lt;/p&gt;
